metadata.name: Knitted geometry or face?
metadata.description:
1/1 Art 

What do you see in front of you? Geometric shapes that hang from above and are at different distances from the eyes? Or a familiar image resembling a human face?

That's how our mind works. From any information that comes to us, be it an image, smells or sounds, our brain forms something that we are familiar with, something that we are used to.
